    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Front Cover, Cooling System, and Related
        Components - Cleaning, Inspection, and Testing - Oil Gerotor Pump
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s09.3.2" svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Oil Gerotor Pump</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Wash all parts thoroughly in a suitable solvent.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, wear safety glasses with side shields. Limit compressed air
                    pressure to 207 kPa (30 psi).
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Dry with filtered compressed air.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lay oil pump housing assembly on workbench.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect inner and outer oil pump gerotors and oil pump housing assembly for nicks, burrs or
                scoring.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Replace any damaged components.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The inner and outer oil pump gerotors are a matched set and cannot be replaced individually.
                    </para>
                </note>
                <note>
                    <para>If installing new inner and outer oil pump gerotors, correct orientation is not necessary. If
                        installing old inner and outer oil pump gerotors, correct orientation is necessary.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place inner and outer oil pump gerotors in oil pump housing assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450009026" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM05/M05127.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Outer oil pump gerotor inspection</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_200.xml" xrefid="s09.t3">feeler gauge</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s09.t3"/>
                to inspect for wear by checking radial clearance between outer oil pump gerotor and oil pump housing
                assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450009027" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM05/M05128.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>End clearance check for oil pump</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check oil pump end clearance as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">With inner and outer oil pump gerotors in place in oil pump housing assembly, put
                    straightedge across housing assembly.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Insert feeler gauge under straightedge at inner and outer oil pump gerotors. Compare end
                    clearance with
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_198.xml" xrefid="s09.t1">specifications</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s09.t1"/>.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">If measurements are not within specifications, replace both inner and outer oil pump
                    gerotors as a set.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove oil pressure regulator.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450009028" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM05/M05132.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil pressure regulator components</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Piston relief</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Spring relief valve</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Cap relief valve and seal relief valve retainer</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect oil pressure regulator components and bore for wear. Replace if necessary.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
